@startuml Neo4j Graph - Complete Architecture
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF

title Neo4j Graph Database - Complete Architecture Model

' Project node
class Project <<Node>> {
  + id : UUID
  + name : String
  + github_url : String
}

' Code entity nodes
class Module <<Node>> {
  + id : UUID
  + name : String
  + path : String
  + language : String
  + complexity : Integer
}

class Class <<Node>> {
  + id : UUID
  + name : String
  + is_abstract : Boolean
  + methods_count : Integer
}

class Function <<Node>> {
  + id : UUID
  + name : String
  + complexity : Integer
  + is_async : Boolean
}

class Interface <<Node>> {
  + id : UUID
  + name : String
}

' Relationships
Project "1" *-- "0..*" Module : CONTAINS
Module "1" *-- "0..*" Class : CONTAINS
Module "1" *-- "0..*" Function : CONTAINS
Class "1" *-- "0..*" Function : CONTAINS

Module "source" --> "target" Module : DEPENDS_ON
Class "source" --> "target" Class : DEPENDS_ON
Function "caller" --> "callee" Function : CALLS

Class "child" --|> "parent" Class : INHERITS
Class "implementer" ..|> "interface" Interface : IMPLEMENTS

note top of Project
  Root node for project
  - Links to all modules
  - Project-level metadata
end note

note right of Module
  Code modules/packages
  - Python: .py files
  - JavaScript: .js/.ts files
  - Java: packages
end note

note right of Class
  Class definitions
  - OOP classes
  - Abstract classes
  - Contains methods
end note

note right of Function
  Functions/Methods
  - Module functions
  - Class methods
  - Async functions
end note

note bottom
  Complete Graph Model Features:
  
  1. Hierarchical Structure:
     Project → Modules → Classes/Functions
  
  2. Dependency Tracking:
     - Module dependencies (imports)
     - Class dependencies (composition)
     - Function dependencies (calls)
  
  3. Inheritance Hierarchy:
     - Class inheritance chains
     - Interface implementations
  
  4. Architectural Analysis:
     - Circular dependency detection
     - Coupling metrics
     - Layer violation detection
     - Dead code identification
  
  5. Query Examples:
     - Find all dependencies of a module
     - Calculate module coupling
     - Detect circular dependencies
     - Find inheritance depth
     - Identify unused functions
end note

@enduml
